Kingsford House is a historic home located at Oswego in Oswego County, New York.   It is a large -story brick residence.  Built about 1870 in the Italianate style, it was extensively reconfigured and enlarged in 1912â€“1913 in the Tudor Revival style. Along the north and east edge of the property is a terrace wall built of cut limestone blocks and topped by a cast and wrought iron fence.
It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1997.
